U.K. Investors Concerned About Complex Pay Measures, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-02-14T02:41:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-14/u-k-investors-concerned-about-complex-pay-measures-ft-reports.html
U.K. institutional investors are
becoming concerned about the complex methods companies use to
calculate management pay, with some measures based on unclear
criteria and others not linked to share price performance, the
Financial Times reported.  “Compensation is going up and I do think that executives
are potentially being very short sighted in this, in a political
context,” Royal London Asset Management Ltd. Chief Investment
Officer Robert Talbut said, according to the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 